.TH CREDENTIALS-MANAGER 1 "2026-05-04" "0.5.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
credentials-manager \- encode, decode, encrypt and decrypt credentials
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B credentials-manager
[\fIcommand\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
A CLI tool for encoding/decoding credentials using Base64, Base32, Hex,
or Base85, and encrypting/decrypting them using Fernet symmetric
encryption.
.PP
Without a command, an interactive menu is launched.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B encode
Encode credentials (username:password) with the specified encoding.
.TP
.B decode
Decode an encoded string back to username and password.
.TP
.B encrypt
Encrypt credentials using Fernet symmetric encryption.
.TP
.B decrypt
Decrypt a Fernet token back to username and password.
.TP
.B keygen
Generate a new Fernet encryption key.
.SH ENCODE OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-username " " \fIUSER\fR
Username (default: empty).
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-password " " \fIPASS\fR
Password (prompted if omitted).
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-file " " \fIFILE\fR
Batch mode: file with one username:password per line.
.TP
.BR \-\-encoding " " \fIENC\fR
Encoding to use: base64, base32, hex, base85 (default: base64).
.TP
.BR \-\-check\-password
Warn if password is weak.
.TP
.BR \-\-format " " \fIFMT\fR
Output format: text, json, env, yaml (default: text).
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Write output to a file.
.SH DECODE OPTIONS
.TP
.I encoded
The encoded string to decode.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-file " " \fIFILE\fR
Batch mode: file with one encoded token per line.
.TP
.BR \-\-encoding " " \fIENC\fR
Encoding used: base64, base32, hex, base85 (default: base64).
.TP
.BR \-\-format " " \fIFMT\fR
Output format: text, json, env, yaml (default: text).
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Write output to a file.
.SH ENCRYPT OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-username " " \fIUSER\fR
Username (default: empty).
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-password " " \fIPASS\fR
Password (prompted if omitted).
.TP
.BR \-\-key " " \fIKEY\fR
Fernet key (or set CREDENTIALS_KEY env var).
.TP
.BR \-\-key\-file " " \fIFILE\fR
File containing the Fernet key.
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Write output to a file.
.SH DECRYPT OPTIONS
.TP
.I token
The Fernet encrypted token.
.TP
.BR \-\-key " " \fIKEY\fR
Fernet key (or set CREDENTIALS_KEY env var).
.TP
.BR \-\-key\-file " " \fIFILE\fR
File containing the Fernet key.
.TP
.BR \-\-format " " \fIFMT\fR
Output format: text, json, env, yaml (default: text).
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Write output to a file.
.SH STDIN
When stdin is piped, encode/decode read from it automatically:
.PP
.nf
echo "admin:secret" | credentials-manager encode
echo "YWRtaW46c2VjcmV0" | credentials-manager decode
.fi
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CREDENTIALS_KEY
Fernet key used by encrypt/decrypt when \-\-key is not provided.
.SH SECURITY
Base64/Base32/Hex/Base85 are NOT encryption. They provide no
cryptographic security. Use the encrypt/decrypt commands with
Fernet for real protection.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
# Encode
credentials-manager encode -u admin -p secret
credentials-manager encode -u admin -p secret --encoding hex

# Decode
credentials-manager decode YWRtaW46c2VjcmV0

# Encrypt
credentials-manager keygen > key.txt
credentials-manager encrypt -u admin -p secret --key-file key.txt
credentials-manager decrypt TOKEN --key-file key.txt

# Batch
credentials-manager encode -f creds.txt --format json -o out.json
.fi
.SH AUTHOR
valorisa <https://github.com/valorisa>
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR base64 (1),
.BR openssl (1)
